At least six people have died in the blaze and more than 70 were injured - of which 20 were in a critical condition. LONDON - Harrowing witness accounts, tales of incredible escapes and a flood of generosity have followed a massive fire that engulfed an apartment block in west London. At least six people have died in the blaze and more than 70 were injured - of which 20 were in a critical condition. Some 250 firefighters battled the flames for hours this morning at the 24-storey Grenfell Tower. London s mayor has described the fire as horrific. The city s fire chief Dany Cotton says there doesn t appear to be any threat of the building collapsing. Investigations will explore the cause of the fire, the evacuation of the building and whether earlier warnings had been ignored.